id: pm-8u2a
title: Ecosystem-wide PM living-context audit & forward-backlog rebuild (2026-06-07)
description: "Manual audit + inspection of ALL 1055 pm items against the entire pm-cli ecosystem (codebase, docs, tests, telemetry, Sentry). Finding: the forward/open backlog is empty again — all 9 capability epics have only closed children, so 'pm context' returns no actionable work, violating the philosophy 'project management = context management'. This plan rebuilds a rich, well-defined, non-duplicate OPEN forward backlog under every capability epic and fills ADR gaps, executed via 5 specialized read+write audit sub-agents (disjoint epic scopes) coordinated by the orchestrator, then shipped as a PR with full AI-bot review loop and merge."
type: Plan
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: 2026-06-07,audit,backlog,context-management,living-map,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-06-07T09:53:26.457Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T11:13:15.201Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-doxj
resolution: "Completed forward-backlog rebuild, PR review loop, merge, and observability verification."
expected_result: "The pm-cli tracker has a non-duplicate living forward backlog across all capability epics, ADR gaps are recorded, PR checks and reviewer state are clean, and main is current after merge."
actual_result: "Created and merged PR #143, added the forward backlog and ADR records, fixed the static secret-scan issue, verified green GitHub checks plus telemetry/Sentry visibility, and closed/released the plan."
